div.p:

                 Anſwere. 
               Nay, it is the worlds wickednes, not our ſtrictnes;

otherwiſe what cauſed the Prophets of God, the Sonne of God himſelf, and his holy Apoſtles to bee ſo much hated and wronged by vngodlie men? They dare not ſay it was their indiſcretion and niſeneſſe, or any the like failing on their part, but in trueth the malice of the wicked, which is the very cauſe why euen in theſe our daies Gods people finde ſuch hard meaſure from prophane perſons.
